race.comment: SHOTGUN BELLA (10) progressive mare who needed the run when returning from a let-up when a narrow second over 1100m at Port Macquarie. Drawn to stalk the tempo and should run the 1400m out. TULIPWOOD (9) disappointed first up at Beaumont (Newcastle), before going to the front for a game win over 1350m at Wyong two weeks ago. Map looks ugly and place prospects best. CHICA DEL MAR (5) underrated mare who broke through for a nice win at Armidale last start. This is obviously harder, but she still has to be included in the main chances. KENMARE BAY (2) will be better over further but still appears capable of sprinting well fresh.
